The best tasting coffee of all Dunkin Donuts I have been to.

Tried the new Beyond Meat Sausage Breakfast Sandwich. The sausage itself was very good and flavorful, but the sandwich was altogether dry. The actual breakfast sandwich comes with egg and cheese, but I'm a vegan so I opted out of the egg and cheese. I will definitely get it again, but maybe next time use grape or strawberry jelly/jam. On the other hand, I usually get an iced coffee with almond milk, a shot of espresso and caramel flavoring, but this particular location didn't execute it very well, so it was very bland.
Never gets the flavoring right. asked and confirmed with us three times and still got it wrong. worst Dunkin experience ever. also happened multiple times.

Store on 50 Pine St, nyc. I was visiting the city and came in for an almond milk coffee and I enquired if anything was vegan. The member of staff just could not be bothered to deal with me and gave me a blunt no. Normally there is something so I politely double checked but she just saw me as a number and wanted to get to next customer. Tell you somerhing they wont need to worry about serving me in the future. After a quick google i believe some bagels may be vegan. Better labelling would also have helped... sale and future customer lost regardless. I wont visit in UK either now!

I usually choose between going to the D&D on Fulton and the one here on Wall Street but I will NOT being going back here. I constantly order the same drink and every time, it tastes different.  The clincher though was this morning when the women behind the counter asked if I wanted their two for $2 special, I thought she meant donuts so I asked for two old fashion donuts, very specific, doesn't leave room for argument. Instead of telling me that it's 2 for $2 on breakfast sandwiches (which I do NOT want), they took my money anyway and then got frustrated with me when I called them out.  Sorry for abandoning you, Fulton Street D&D, I'm coming back to you.

Service is usually quick, but the drinks are inconsistently made.  I usually get the caramel latte.  It is very inconsistent.  Sometimes it has hardly any caramel, sometimes it is loaded with caramel.  They never ask what kind of milk so this time they just used what the guy in front of me got (skim - yuck).  However, the location is very convenient to my job so I guess I'll keep going.
